   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Hard water, or water with high levels of calcium and magnesium
ions, encourages the formation of insoluble chemical compounds by
combining with cooling system additives such as silicates and
phosphates.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The tendency of silicates and phosphates to precipitate
out-of-solution increases with increasing water hardness. Hard
water, or water with high levels of calcium and magnesium ions
encourages the formation of insoluble chemicals, especially after a
number of heating and cooling cycles.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Time prefers the use of distilled water or deionized water to
reduce the potential and severity of chemical insolubility.</p>
